The paper deals with the knapsack problem, which is a classic problem in computer science and falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The problem involves optimization and approximation, which are also topics in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper presents an FPTAS, which involves analyzing the running time and complexity of the algorithm, making it relevant to computational complexity (cs.CC). The problem also involves optimization and decision-making, which are topics in game theory (cs.GT). Finally, the paper involves the use of mathematical tools and techniques, such as affine functions and real-valued parameters, which are relevant to information theory (cs.IT).
